name: Sprouting Weeds
category: Terrain
footprint: 1x1
facing: no
shadow: no
blocks_light: no
height: 0.15
placement: floor
room_types: ruined-watchtower, cabin-abandoned, ancient-ruin-overgrown, crypt
typical_count: many
clusters_with: fallen-leaves, moss-patch, fern-cluster, bush-berry, rubble-pile
notes: Weeds and tiny plants pushing up through floor cracks. Signals that a place has been abandoned long enough for nature to reclaim. Scatter across ruined interiors.
---
# footprint 1x1: x range 0-1, y range 0-1
# Top-down: small leafy sprouts and grass tufts emerging from hinted floor cracks.

# Hint of cracked floor beneath (thin dark stroke lines, no fill)
line 0.12,0.34 0.44,0.42 stroke #1a1410 0.55 width 1
line 0.44,0.42 0.58,0.28 stroke #1a1410 0.45 width 1
line 0.56,0.60 0.86,0.72 stroke #1a1410 0.55 width 1
line 0.30,0.68 0.52,0.82 stroke #1a1410 0.45 width 1

# === Grass tuft 1 (NW) — narrow blades radiating from a root point ===
line 0.22,0.40 0.18,0.26 stroke #3a6a2a width 2
line 0.22,0.40 0.24,0.24 stroke #4a7a3a width 2
line 0.22,0.40 0.30,0.26 stroke #3a6a2a width 2
line 0.22,0.40 0.14,0.30 stroke #4a7a3a width 1
# Small base leaf
poly 0.18,0.40 0.22,0.38 0.26,0.40 0.22,0.44 fill #3a6a2a 0.85
poly 0.18,0.40 0.22,0.38 0.26,0.40 0.22,0.44 stroke #1a3a10

# === Leafy sprout (NE) — 3 small leaves from a stem ===
